reviews.text:
Service is not bad, restaurant atmosphere  is not bad, but the food there is not good.  Especially pizza, can tell it is not freshly made, it should be reheated.  Seafood is not fresh too, mussel and prawn are not just the frozen one, it is really bad quality.  
Sadly, the food they served really like microwave food.  I understood during night time the business is poor, still you are selling food, food quality is indeed very important.
The environment is nice. Service is fine. The food is good!

This restaurant charges a reasonable price for all the menu food.  You can choose salad, soap, steaks, and so on.  For the steaks, the restaurant provides many type of steak to choose.  They are from US.  And some are from Japan, which are more expensive.  I have tried the mid price range, the chef cook very well and taste great.  The overall restaurant is very spacious, and would not feel crowded.  Last but not least , the dessert I have tried is the milk pudding.   Also good to try.  And per person, it is about 200+ , for each dinner course.
Good food and fair price for lunch

Table setting is incorrect for Italian or Western cuisine.  Fish is plain, had to ask for salt and pepper. Table service was slow with water. Burger was raw, very dangerous, not even McDonald's would take that risk. Unnecessary drink lighting.  Be safe and order the all day breakfast.  Soup was nice the price was not. Music could have been simpler, jazz or lounge would have been better.
